<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-314-104  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 314 104.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  April 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Montreal group launches EDI effort. (Electronic Data Interchangefor Commerce)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industryCanadaElectronic data interchangeElectronic Data Interchange for CommerceResearch and DevelopmentPlanningTransportation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MONTREAL GROUP LAUNCHES EDI EFFORT MONTREAL, QUEBEC, CANADA, 1990 MAR 30 (NB)-- A group of private companies and public-sector organizations has launchedElectronic Data Interchange for Commerce (EDICOM), an effort to develop anelectronic data interchange system for transportation and related sectorshere.andM;The effort involves the Port of Montreal, the Montreal Chamber of Commerce,Customs Canada, several private shipping and transport firms and Canada's twomajor railways.andM;The EDICOM group has budgeted C$3.23 million for analysis, technologyacquisition and design and pilot implementation.andP;  Full implementation willfollow.andP;  EDICOM expects the provincial and federal governments to pay abouthalf the cost of the first phase, trading system analysis, which is expectedto take about nine months.andM;At the same time, the Montreal Chamber of Commerce announced a campaign tomake business people aware of EDI.andP;  A group of prominent business executiveshave agreed to sponsor this project.andM;(Grant Buckler/19900330/Press Contact: Port of Montreal Public RelationsDept., 514-283-7050; Montreal Chamber of Commerce, 514- 288-9090)</TEXT></DOC>